{"googleAnalytics": ["UA-30227798-9"], "version": "6", "submitlog": "math spacing and splash class", "abstract": "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" xmlns:c=\"http://cnx.rice.edu/cnxml\" xmlns:md=\"http://cnx.rice.edu/mdml\" xmlns:qml=\"http://cnx.rice.edu/qml/1.0\" xmlns:mod=\"http://cnx.rice.edu/#moduleIds\" xmlns:bib=\"http://bibtexml.sf.net/\" xmlns:data=\"http://dev.w3.org/html5/spec/#custom\"/>", "revised": "2020-08-18T18:03:40Z", "printStyle": null, "roles": null, "keywords": ["slope-intercept form", "point-slope form", "interpolation", "correlation coefficient", "extrapolation", "slope", "decreasing function", "increasing function", "least squares regression", "linear function", "model breakdown", "parallel lines", "perpendicular lines", "vertical line"], "id": "792137bd-4949-4250-b424-831863286a93", "canonical": "fd53eae1-fa23-47c7-bb1b-972349835c3c", "title": "Introduction to Linear Functions", "mediaType": "application/vnd.org.cnx.module", "canon_url": "https://staging.cnx.org/contents/fd53eae1-fa23-47c7-bb1b-972349835c3c:792137bd-4949-4250-b424-831863286a93/Introduction-to-Linear-Functions", "content": "<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">\n<head xmlns:c=\"http://cnx.rice.edu/cnxml\" xmlns:md=\"http://cnx.rice.edu/mdml\"><title>Introduction to Linear Functions</title><meta name=\"created-time\" content=\"2014/02/20 17:38:03 -0600\"/><meta name=\"revised-time\" content=\"2014/11/23 12:34:34 -0600\"/><meta name=\"license\" content=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/\"/><meta name=\"keywords\" content=\"correlation coefficient, decreasing function, extrapolation, increasing function, interpolation, least squares regression, linear function, model breakdown, parallel lines, perpendicular lines, point-slope form, slope, slope-intercept form, vertical line\"/><meta name=\"subject\" content=\"Mathematics and Statistics\"/></head>\n\n<body xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" xmlns:c=\"http://cnx.rice.edu/cnxml\" xmlns:md=\"http://cnx.rice.edu/mdml\" xmlns:qml=\"http://cnx.rice.edu/qml/1.0\" xmlns:mod=\"http://cnx.rice.edu/#moduleIds\" xmlns:bib=\"http://bibtexml.sf.net/\" xmlns:data=\"http://www.w3.org/TR/html5/dom.html#custom-data-attribute\" xmlns:epub=\"http://www.idpf.org/2007/ops\" class=\"introduction\" data-cnxml-to-html-ver=\"2.1.0\"><div data-type=\"document-title\">Introduction to Linear Functions</div><cnx-pi data-type=\"cnx.flag.introduction\">\n        class=\"introduction\"\n      </cnx-pi>\n<cnx-pi data-type=\"cnx.eoc\">class=\"key-equations\" title=\"Key Equations\"</cnx-pi>\n<cnx-pi data-type=\"cnx.eoc\">class=\"key-concepts\" title=\"Key Concepts\"</cnx-pi>\n<cnx-pi data-type=\"cnx.eoc\">class=\"review-exercises\" title=\"Review Exercises\"</cnx-pi>\n<cnx-pi data-type=\"cnx.eoc\">class=\"practice-test\" title=\"Practice Test\"</cnx-pi>\n<cnx-pi data-type=\"cnx.answers\">class=\"try\"</cnx-pi>\n<cnx-pi data-type=\"cnx.answers\">class=\"section-exercises\"</cnx-pi>\n\n<figure id=\"CNX_Precalc_02_00_01\" class=\"splash unnumbered\" data-label=\"\"><figcaption>A bamboo forest in China (credit: &#8220;JFXie&#8221;/Flickr)</figcaption>\n<span data-type=\"media\" id=\"fs-id2381652\" data-alt=\"An upward view of bamboo trees.\">\n<img src=\"/resources/ab9ae8c1baf04f88efa903c8786123d977e38f06/CNX_Precalc_02_00_01.jpg\" data-media-type=\"image/jpg\" alt=\"An upward view of bamboo trees.\"/>\n</span>\n\n</figure>\n\n<p id=\"fs-id1165137705130\">Imagine placing a plant in the ground one day and finding that it has doubled its height just a few days later. Although it may seem incredible, this can happen with certain types of bamboo species. These members of the grass family are the fastest-growing plants in the world. One species of bamboo has been observed to grow nearly 1.5 inches every hour.<a href=\"#ch02_mod00_fn01\" role=\"doc-noteref\" epub:type=\"noteref\">[footnote]</a> In a twenty-four hour period, this bamboo plant grows about 36 inches, or an incredible 3 feet! A constant rate of change, such as the growth cycle of this bamboo plant, is a linear function.</p><aside role=\"doc-footnote\" epub:type=\"footnote\" id=\"ch02_mod00_fn01\">http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/records-3000/fastest-growing-plant/</aside>\n<p id=\"fs-id1165137605883\">Recall from <a href=\"/contents/11f4eacc-c348-4836-8c5b-747577d249ca\" class=\"target-chapter\">Functions and Function Notation</a> that a function is a relation that assigns to every element in the domain exactly one element in the range. Linear functions are a specific type of function that can be used to model many real-world applications, such as plant growth over time. In this chapter, we will explore linear functions, their graphs, and how to relate them to data.</p></body>\n\n</html>", "subjects": ["Mathematics and Statistics"], "legacy_id": "m49321", "parentId": null, "resources": [{"media_type": "text/xml", "id": "9fc77952b9ced28561e05b37ddbe174c76ee56ce", "filename": "index.cnxml"}, {"media_type": "image/jpeg", "id": "ab9ae8c1baf04f88efa903c8786123d977e38f06", "filename": "CNX_Precalc_02_00_01.jpg"}, {"media_type": "text/html", "id": "e92857d6752ee9aab054166bc979ce626acdfa41", "filename": "index.cnxml.html"}], "publishers": [{"surname": "OpenStax College", "suffix": "", "firstname": "", "title": "", "fullname": "OpenStax", "id": "OpenStaxCollege"}, {"surname": "Precalculus", "suffix": "", "firstname": "OpenStax College", "title": "", "fullname": "OpenStax College Precalculus", "id": "cnxprecal"}], "parent": {"authors": [], "shortId": null, "version": "", "id": null, "title": null}, "stateid": 1, "parentTitle": null, "shortId": "eSE3vUlJ", "authors": [{"surname": "OpenStax College", "suffix": "", "firstname": "", "title": "", "fullname": "OpenStax", "id": "OpenStaxCollege"}, {"surname": "Precalculus", "suffix": "", "firstname": "OpenStax College", "title": "", "fullname": "OpenStax College Precalculus", "id": "cnxprecal"}], "parentVersion": "", "legacy_version": "1.6", "licensors": [{"surnam